uence at GATC (SUPREMERUN) using the forward primers.<\/p>\n\n<p>After blasting the reads to refseq, I see that they are ~30% shorter than the PCR product. Example: <\/p>\n\n<p>PCR expected length = 182 bp\nRead length = 133 bp<\/p>\n\n<p>I must mention that in the gels the expected PCR sizes were ok.<\/p>\n\n<p>Does anyone have an idea what is the reason for this decrease in length?<\/p>\n\n<p>Thanks<\/p>\n","question_id":42640,"tags":["dna-sequencing","pcr","blast"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":42642,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":57,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6e1676239f1e00d91b71b834d2f8a05b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3627,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3627/ovi","reputation":145,"display_name":"Ovi","accept_rate":75},"closed_date":1453711248,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":42639,"edited":false,"creation_date":1453707303,"comment_id":73385,"body":"I think this will be better suited on health.stackexchange. If there are no objections, I will migrate this question."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6e1676239f1e00d91b71b834d2f8a05b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3627,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3627/ovi","reputation":145,"display_name":"Ovi","accept_rate":75},"score":0,"post_id":42639,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1453709285,"comment_id":73387,"body":"@C