e theoretical one. <\/p>\n\n<p><em>This could get more complicated/interesting as new medical therapies mature.  If one were to clone a human for example, is that a type of reproduction? Likewise, there is gene therapy, which could overcome some types of genetic-based sterility.<\/em><\/p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Sources:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/Infertility\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/Infertility<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/sterility\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/sterility<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.acog.org/~/media/For%20Patients/faq011.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.acog.org/~/media/For%20Patients/faq011.pdf<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","answer_id":42596,"question_id":42593,"up_vote_count":3}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/42593/what-is-working-definition-for-female-infertility","last_activity_date":1453569862,"creation_date":1453566805,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is working definition for female infertility?","body":"<p>I've studied infertility and found that its quite complex to define. However, I came to know about a useful working definition of infertility; which was \" Failure to achieve pregnancy\".\nFew days later I've hit upon a idea that proves that definition wrong. As I studied the turner syndrome, in which condition was XO but individual was infertile female. Further I studied that if they are subsequently treated with Gonadotrophin hormones, they have menstrual periods as well. There I found that if a fertilized egg is implanted in their uterus, pregnancy would be achieved. Now how would we call that female infertile?<\/p>\n","question_id":42593,"tags":["genetics","reproduction"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":42596,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":41,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/a