ring all options (eg. exponential, untransformed, etc).  <\/p>\n\n<p>Does anyone know of any good recent synthesis work on how to choose the best model?  Of particular interest are the assumptions behind each model, and the ecological mechanisms that each model might imply.<\/p>\n","question_id":42298,"tags":["ecology","theoretical-biology","landscape-ecology"],"score":3,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":24,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1452774041},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/FpmrT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15882,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15882/st-vincent","reputation":138,"display_name":"St Vincent"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10456/march-ho","reputation":5867,"display_name":"March Ho","accept_rate":80},"score":2,"post_id":34469,"edited":false,"creation_date":1432330436,"comment_id":55290,"body":"I think this is the wrong way of looking at the question. Neurotoxins are more lethal (have a lower LD50) because less of it is required to kill the organism due to their specific action."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/FpmrT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15882,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15882/st-vincent","reputation":138,"display_name":"St Vincent"},"score":0,"post_id":34469,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10456/march-ho","reputation":5867,"display_name":"March Ho","accept_rate":80},"edited":false,"creation_date":1432331892,"comment_id":55292,"body":"@March Ho I figured it wasn&#39;t that simple. My chemistry/biology knowledge is very limited"}],"answers":[{