 enter the egg before the jelly formation. For this purpose the sperms should remain in as close a contact with egg is possible. The copulation is essential in frogs, in order to provide the maximum possible number of eggs, an opportunity for fertilization within a very short time, therefore they possesses copulatory pads.The male frog holds the female frog firmly by its forelimbs and nuptial pads. Thus having copulatory pads is advantageous and important for more eggs to be fertilised.<\/p>\n","answer_id":41906,"question_id":41904,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1453214235}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/41904/why-do-male-frogs-have-a-copulatory-pad","last_activity_date":1453214235,"creation_date":1451524170,"answer_count":1,"title":"Why do male frogs have a copulatory pad?","body":"<p>In frogs fertilisation is external, It does not make sense in having copulatory pad in male frogs?<\/p>\n","question_id":41904,"tags":["zoology"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":41906,"down_vote_count":2,"closed_reason":"unclear what you're asking","is_answered":true,"view_count":159,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1451572960},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f7f09ec1f6f4ff748b51ee33a753af75?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10193,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10193/vonjd","reputation":441,"display_name":"vonjd","accept_rate":100},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/210cc4a4b2f281aaffe0b26521fe1ab8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1590,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":0,"post_id":42194,"edited":false,"creation_date":1452424275,"comment_id":72248,"body":"Could you clarify point 2 for me please, individuals don&#39;t evolve. Do you mean that mutations/immigrants is allowed to affect variation in fitness?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"http