owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/68562a81029f7c590c13339df1f7db98?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1004,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1004/martin-beracochea","reputation":246,"display_name":"Martin Beracochea"},"score":2,"post_id":8682,"edited":false,"creation_date":1370621892,"comment_id":11138,"body":"An idea: dead bodies attract potentially dangerous animals. So hide them underground was a strategy to protect the group."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1MUb2.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1306/terdon","reputation":9339,"display_name":"terdon","accept_rate":73},"score":4,"post_id":8682,"edited":false,"creation_date":1370638504,"comment_id":11141,"body":"Guys, dead bodies stink. Quite apart from our innate disgust and questions of hygiene, having dead bodies lying around is extremely unpleasant because they smell bad."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f437d9a11deebd214089822c26197f35?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3553,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3553/james","reputation":4533,"display_name":"James","accept_rate":83},"score":1,"post_id":8682,"edited":false,"creation_date":1453107765,"comment_id":72941,"body":"Are you asking why we decided to bury rather than burn them or eat them, or why we get rid of the bodies at all? As it stands the question is unclear to me. A citation would be great as to where you heard this too."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/53c30bc1f1ac4e6b256e52b62124da86?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1757,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1757/androidpenguin","reputation":4652,"display_name":"AndroidPenguin","accept_rate":25},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ba800182f97b0bd5a